FIGURES 157–168 
<taxonomicName authority="Henry &amp; Bøggild, 2021" authorityName="Henry &amp; Bøggild" authorityYear="2021" box="[366,547,1943,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neuter" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[366,547,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="327">Megaselia neuter</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[554,608,1944,1967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="327" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
male. 157, frons; 158, detail of part of frons; 159, antennae, palps and proboscis; 160, proboscis from below; 161, side of thorax; 162, abdomen; 163, left face of hypopygium; 164, left face of epandrium and hypandrium; 165, right face of hypopygium; 166, front tarsus; 167, hind femur; 168, wing; 162, Haltere.
